        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Greensboro, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
McLeansville, Greensboro, Lake Guilford Mackintosh Marina, Forest
Oaks, Alamance, Elon, Lake Jeanette Marina, Lake Mackintosh Marina,
Burlington, and Pleasant Garden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
